TravisBuddy Request Identifier: ebe0e750-e520-11e9-950a-c74496fc22d4Hey, I was using the module recently and was going to add types anyway, and then came across this!
Is there any way that the PaginatedList class could be made generic, and then narrowed when it’s returned so the values pulled from it are also typed?
I’ll follow up with examples if needed tomorrow.I'm really not sure if generics can work only with stubs @Richard-Lynch
In any case, I think it's a good idea, but maybe it should be done as "step 2".I actually didn't realise that, my bad!
I'll keep an eye for step 2, is there an issue I can watch for the depreciation of Py2 support?
Body:
Adds type stubs that can be used in mypy, as requested in: #1217
The current type stubs were generated by MonkeyType against the unit test, however it missed a few things here and there so manual fix is required before merging (still WIP).

Body:
It resolves #1208. Fixing it is not as easy as it looks like. Currently PyGithub tries to use a common way to request GitHub v3 API.

  
    
      PyGithub/github/Repository.py
    
    
        Lines 725 to 739
      in
      74cd685
    
    
    
    

        
          
               @property 
        

        
          
               def topics(self): 
        

        
          
                   """ 
        

        
          
                   :type: list of strings 
        

        
          
                   """ 
        

        
          
                   self._completeIfNotSet(self._topics) 
        

        
          
                   return self._topics.value 
        

        
          
            
        

        
          
               @property 
        

        
          
               def trees_url(self): 
        

        
          
                   """ 
        

        
          
                   :type: string 
        

        
          
                   """ 
        

        
          
                   self._completeIfNotSet(self._trees_url) 
        

        
          
                   return self._trees_url.value 
        
    
  


Due to GitHub preview handling, each individual preview has its own MIME type(the Accept header) to enable it. I'm not sure it's good to use some MIME type by default. If I put the mercy-preview in default Accept header, there will be 33 fail tests. And if GitHub adds some new preview, we need to change the ReplayData again.
If any good idea, please tell me, I will change.

Title: Label API: pass custom media type in the Accept header

Thank you for the feedback. After taking more time to understand the code flow, I realize that I misplaced my fix. The encoding issue was in for the _url field in ContentFile. When this _url is used by the GithubObject:__complete method it isn't properly sanitized. It only affects ContentFile not all GithubObjects.
Here is a test case demonstrating the issue:
g = github.Github(ACCESS_TOKEN)
r = g.search_code("user:nbsullivan GIFShare_es")
print(r[0].decoded_content)

This produces the following error:

I would add it to ContentFile's test, but don't encode # into the test name, just make it descriptive enough testEncodeWithSpecialCharacters or something close.Added a test case and the associated replay data. I hope it is close to what you had in mind. Thank you!
Body:
PyGithub currently fails on content retrieval due to '#' characters in URL path. This code path is hit when using GitHub code search and GithubObject.py:__complete is retrieving the i-th repo for decoded_content.
I fixed it similar to other instances in the codebase using urllib.parse.quote.
Example of search result that cannot be retrieved:
https://github.com/nbsullivan/hashtagcluster/blob/71c978ee41dc1ccdbdba8ee93507a2e418798ece/data/results/emmybatchpreds/#Emmys_batch5080usercount.csv
Returned from code search query:
"user:nbsullivan GIFShare_es"
